  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Brand voice is the consistent personality and style of an organization\u0026rsquo;s writing across all its communications — website copy, emails, social media, documentation, error messages. It is voice applied at institutional scale: the distinctive way an organization sounds when it writes.\nBrand voice has two dimensions:\nVoice — the consistent personality traits. A brand might be \u0026ldquo;confident but not arrogant,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;friendly but not informal,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;expert but not jargon-heavy.\u0026rdquo; These traits remain constant across all content. Tone — how the voice adapts to context. The same brand voice sounds different in a celebratory announcement than in an apology, in a marketing email than in a support article. Voice is who you are; tone is how you speak to the current situation. Brand voice guidelines typically specify:\n",
